Data model (minimal)
// types.ts
type Business = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  vertical: string;      // e.g. "wellness"
  metro: string;         // e.g. "Austin"
  offer: string;
  need: string;
  verified: boolean;
  outcomeScore: number;  // 0-5
};
type Trade = {
  id: string;
  fromId: string;
  toId: string;
  status: "proposed" | "completed";
  rating?: number;
};
Seed 10 businesses so matches always exist (include 2 obvious pairs + 1 triangle).

AI prompt (single route /api/match)
You are Reciproca, a B2B trade matcher. Given:
OFFER: {offer}
NEED: {need}
CANDIDATES: {json list of 3 businesses}
Return JSON: { "matches": [{ "id", "score", "reason" }] }
Reason must be one sentence, plain English, no jargon.
If API fails → show rule-based matches + static reason strings (still demoable).

